<head>TURBAN</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">頭巾</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">巾</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>HAT in the form of a CLOTH TIED AROUND the HEAD.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general word for a turban is jīn 巾, and this type of headgear is worn as the only headgear.</p>
<p>2. Zé 幘 is rare in pre-Han times and refers to a piece of thin silk with which to stabilise the hair-bun which parts of which might hang down over the shoulders and down to the eyebrows. Above the zé 幘 one might, occasionally, wear a guān 冠 "hat".</p>
        </div>
